  "text": "Rainfall trends varied considerably from year to year but showed an overall decline in annual rainfall from a peak in 1974 (Fig. 2) . Rainfall trends were similar between the NE and NW core. Calf production declined in both regions during the late 1970s in response to the Bovine Tuberculosis Eradication Campaign (BTEC) which destocked the entire NSA area of cattle by the early 1980s [CITATION_1] . Restocking then occurred in both regions, reaching peak calf production around 1989.",
